<h3 class="endpoint">
    GET /api/v1/users/:user_id/avatars
  </h3>
<p>A paginated list of the possible user avatar options that can be set with
the user update endpoint. The response will be an array of avatar records.
If the 'type' field is 'attachment', the record will
include all the normal attachment json fields; otherwise it will include
only the 'url' and 'display_name' fields. Additionally, all
records will include a 'type' field and a 'token' field.
The following explains each field in more detail</p>
